        "locked": false,
        "title": "Add an autofix or generator for missing config field labels",
        "body": "## Problem\n\n`src/config/schema.help.quality.test.ts` fails when new help keys are added without corresponding entries in `FIELD_LABELS`. A recent example was `gateway.push`, which caused CI failures until labels were added manually.\n\n## Why It Matters\n\n- The current workflow is easy to forget during unrelated feature work.\n- Contributors often learn about the missing label only after CI fails.\n- The fix is usually mechanical, but still requires manual hunting and edits.\n\n## Suggested Direction\n\nAdd a better developer workflow for label parity, for example:\n\n- a small generator/scaffold command for missing labels\n- or a test failure that prints copy-paste-ready label stubs\n- or a stricter schema-driven source for labels/help metadata\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Adding a new help key makes the required label update obvious.\n- Fixing missing labels is quick and mechanical.\n- CI failures around label parity become easier to diagnose and resolve.\n",
